						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarāja-Rājakēsarivarman I: Year 12 = 996-97 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is slightly damaged. </p>						

						<p>It refers to the king as ‘who destroyed the ships at Śālai’.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of a silver image (of the god ?) weighing 424 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju,</hi> and a copper image of Chaṇḍēśvaradēvan weighing 500 <hi rend="italic">palam,</hi> by a certain Nakkaṉ Nallatt-aḍigaḷ, a member of the <hi rend="italic">Irājarājatteriñja-kaikkōḷa</hi> community, who was the son of Aṇukkaṉ Mahamalli, a <hi rend="italic">peṇḍāṭṭi</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">vēḷam</hi> of Irāsakēsaripanmar.</p>						

						</summary>
